post_text:
Grab & Go Meals!!

Beginning March 23, 2020, Schleswig Community School is offering free grab & go meals to all children ages 0-18. Child must be present in order for meals to be provided. Please help us practice social distancing at distribution locations, along with other recommended guidelines by the CDC.
Pick up locations will be as follows:
Mondays-Wednesdays-Fridays: At the Schleswig School, south entrance (by the Superintendent’s office), 11 am-noon
Tuesdays & Thursdays-in the parking lot of the Ricketts Community Center, 11 am-noon

Meals will be offered during the COVID 19 related school closure time period. The school building is closed to the public, staff will not be available to answer questions. Meals may NOT be consumed on school grounds, plan to take meals home. If you have questions, you can call the school at 712-676-3313.

CHILD CARE MEETING - SATURDAY, MARCH 28th at 1:30 at the SCHLESWIG COMMUNITY BUILDING.
The community of Schleswig is exploring starting a child care center. A meeting will be held Saturday, March 28 at 1:30 in the Schleswig Community Building. The Program Director for Early Childhood Iowa for Crawford, Sac, and Buena Vista Counties along with Representatives from Iowa Child Care Resource and Referral will be in attendance. Those interested in hearing about this endeavor and either being on the child care board or in a support capacity is urged to attend.

Next week is "Read Across America Week." Each day is a different dress up day.
Monday - "Oh the Place You Will Go!" - What do you want to be when you grow up?
Tuesday - "My Many Colored Days" - Wear as many colors as you can.
Wednesday - "I am NOT Going to Get Up!!" - Wear appropriate pajamas or comfy clothes.
Thursday - "How the Grinch Stole Christmas" - Wear a Christmas shirt/ugly sweater.
Friday - "If I Ran the Zoo" - Wear animal print, something you would wear to the zoo or dress up like someone who works at the zoo.

post_text:
Schleswig Visual Artists

Schleswig Middle School Visual Artists entered the Sioux City Art Center’s 30th Annual Juried Youth Art Exhibition: Middle School, 2020. The selection was made from nearly 200 artworks entered narrowing the accepted artworks to 56
works for the show. Being a very selective show, Schleswig had 3 artworks accepted for the show: Riley Miller – alcohol ink, Adayla Schultz – leaf print, and Anna Galvin – sun print. This show will be exhibited from February 15 – April 12,
2020. The reception will be held Sunday, February 16, 1:30 – 3:00.

Pictured are: Front Row: Kezia Mullen, Hunter Wilson Second Row: Malachi Esteves, Kysa Neddermeyer, Rachee Nar, Anna Galvin, Owen Galvin Third Row: Isabella Clark, Deserae Safarian (2), Eryn Wilson, Brock Schneider (2), Adayla Schultz Fourth Row: Calli Korner (2), Marissa Galvin, Riley Miller (2), and Elli Heiden. Visual Art Teacher – Mrs. Twyla Godbersen TK-8th

post_text:
Twelve Schleswig vocal music students will travel to Underwood, IA on March 10th to participate in the Southwest Iowa Choral Directors Association Middle School Honor Choir festival. The participating students have been rehearsing once a week to learn the challenging music planned for the production.

The concert begins at 7:00 p.m. at the Underwood High School gymnasium. There is an admission charge to the event. The concert will feature a 5-6th grade choir, under the direction of Christina Svec, and a 7-8th grade choir, under the direction of Tom Gerking. Congratulations to these musicians!

post_text:
Malachi Esteves has been selected for participation in the 34th annual statewide Opus Honor Choir Festival. This is the highest vocal honor for middle school students across the state of Iowa. He was one of the 720 participants accepted out of over 2,600 Iowa students that auditioned. The 2019 Opus Honor Choirs will perform at 4:00 p.m. on Thursday, November 21st in C.Y. Stephens Auditorium at Iowa State University in Ames.

Have Fun Malachi!!

HOMECOMING PARADE UPDATE!!!!!

Due to the projected forecast and low temps on Friday, the Denison High School Homecoming Parade has been rescheduled from Friday October 11th to Wednesday, October 9th this week.
We will follow the same time schedule as originally set for Friday, with the same line-up procedures and same route through downtown. Those planning on still riding in the Parade, please line-up approx. 1:30 on 1st Ave. North by the Post Office. Buses will still run at their regular time on Wednesday.

post_text:
The 5th graders were awarded a 2nd Project Jack grant to "Pay it Forward" in their communities by the Realtors Foundation of Iowa. For the 2nd grant the class chose to work with Crossroads of Crawford County. The class was able to purchase $250 worth of supplies for Crossroads of Crawford County and Lutheran Servies in Iowa's Lending Closet. The Lending Closet is for foster and/or adoptive parents of children placed into their home. The closet will be used as a place parents may go to for needed supplies. The class was able to purchase toliet paper, toothbrushes, toothpaste, bubble bath, stuffed animals, pillows, blankets, underwear, socks, and few clothing items. They also contributed two tie blankets they had made. Also included are colorful encouragement cards. It's always great when kids are able to help other kids like them!

Thank you Janette Clausen & Jac Friedrichsen for coming to accept these donations & tell their stories!!
